1
00:00:06,072 --> 00:00:09,140
The nervous system
is fundamentally electric.

2
00:00:09,141 --> 00:00:10,375
When we move our arm,

3
00:00:10,376 --> 00:00:11,676
it moves because a signal

4
00:00:11,677 --> 00:00:13,211
has been sent to the muscle

5
00:00:13,212 --> 00:00:14,512
that controls it,

6
00:00:14,513 --> 00:00:16,414
and that message
is made of charged atoms

7
00:00:16,415 --> 00:00:19,150
moving in and out
of nerve cells.

8
00:00:19,151 --> 00:00:20,852
It's electricity.

9
00:00:20,853 --> 00:00:22,554
Now, because the brain
is electric,

10
00:00:22,555 --> 00:00:24,756
we could also use
electricity to record

11
00:00:24,757 --> 00:00:26,524
what the brain is doing

12
00:00:26,525 --> 00:00:28,860
or bypass it entirely,

13
00:00:28,861 --> 00:00:31,629
-and control a body.
-[beep]

14
00:00:31,630 --> 00:00:33,865
That means that
we could use our minds

15
00:00:33,866 --> 00:00:36,334
to move other people's bodies,

16
00:00:36,335 --> 00:00:38,736
restore movement to people
who are paralyzed,

17
00:00:38,737 --> 00:00:41,473
feel through an artificial hand
as if it was our own,

18
00:00:41,474 --> 00:00:44,776
and even read people's minds.

19
00:00:44,777 --> 00:00:46,377
Shocking!

20
00:00:46,378 --> 00:01:07,732
[theme music playing]

21
00:01:07,733 --> 00:01:09,434
Even though electricity

22
00:01:09,435 --> 00:01:10,635
wasn't really understood

23
00:01:10,636 --> 00:01:12,237
until the 1800s,

24
00:01:12,238 --> 00:01:14,405
its ability
to influence the body

25
00:01:14,406 --> 00:01:15,740
had been known since at least

26
00:01:15,741 --> 00:01:17,308
ancient Roman times,

27
00:01:17,309 --> 00:01:18,776
when respected physician

28
00:01:18,777 --> 00:01:20,645
Scribonius Largus

29
00:01:20,646 --> 00:01:21,779
 wrote about a man

30
00:01:21,780 --> 00:01:23,348
 who accidentally stepped

31
00:01:23,349 --> 00:01:24,816
 on an electric fish

32
00:01:24,817 --> 00:01:27,785
 and was suddenly relieved
 of gout pain.

33
00:01:27,786 --> 00:01:29,487
Scribonius did some experiments

34
00:01:29,488 --> 00:01:31,789
and found that you could put
an electric fish

35
00:01:31,790 --> 00:01:35,560
 on your head
 and relieve headaches.

36
00:01:35,561 --> 00:01:36,928
In 1804,

37
00:01:36,929 --> 00:01:38,530
centuries later,

38
00:01:38,531 --> 00:01:40,832
 Italian physicist
 Giovanni Aldini

39
00:01:40,833 --> 00:01:43,401
 discovered he could make
 people's muscles move

40
00:01:43,402 --> 00:01:45,170
 with electricity.

41
00:01:45,171 --> 00:01:46,504
He amazed the European world

42
00:01:46,505 --> 00:01:47,739
by using electricity

43
00:01:47,740 --> 00:01:49,374
to animate the corpse

44
00:01:49,375 --> 00:01:50,942
of an executed criminal.

45
00:01:50,943 --> 00:01:53,211
 The corpse opened its eyes

46
00:01:53,212 --> 00:01:55,547
 and even seemed to sit up.

47
00:01:55,548 --> 00:01:59,284
But Aldini wasn't just
trying to shock people.

48
00:01:59,285 --> 00:02:01,452
He was showing the world
that neurons,

49
00:02:01,453 --> 00:02:02,887
the cells that control both

50
00:02:02,888 --> 00:02:05,223
our thoughts and our movements,

51
00:02:05,224 --> 00:02:07,725
operate through electricity.

52
00:02:07,726 --> 00:02:17,702
[buzzing]

53
00:02:17,703 --> 00:02:20,805
Imagine bypassing
a person's brain

54
00:02:20,806 --> 00:02:24,375
so as to control their body.

55
00:02:24,376 --> 00:02:25,810
Now normally
when you move your body,

56
00:02:25,811 --> 00:02:27,812
your brain sends
electrical signals

57
00:02:27,813 --> 00:02:29,247
through nerves.

58
00:02:29,248 --> 00:02:30,982
But if we could use electrodes

59
00:02:30,983 --> 00:02:32,350
